name: methyl_butyl_ether
source: American Petroleum Institute. Research Project 44; Selected Values of Properties of Hydrocarbons and Related Compounds. Texas A & M University; College Station; TX; 1973.
Reason: 1,1-Dimethoxyethane (methyl ethyl ether) has a melting point of -114.1°C. The methyl group introduces a rigid structure and raises the melting point due to increased molecular weight and van der Waals interactions. The ethyl group also contributes to the melting point due to its ability to participate in hydrogen bonding.
